Is anyone there?

13
00:01:23,110 --> 00:01:25,300
Excuse me

14
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:29,260
I have something to ask.

15
00:01:29,260 --> 00:01:31,900
Is no one here?

16
00:01:32,660 --> 00:01:36,580
Why is the door open and no one is here?

17
00:01:39,660 --> 00:01:41,580
 Chicken QC Contest

18
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,930
What?

19
00:01:47,380 --> 00:01:52,320
 Chicken QC Contest 
First Place Winner

20
00:02:06,090 --> 00:02:07,890
 Let's go.

21
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:28,860
When did you wake up and make all this?

22
00:02:28,860 --> 00:02:32,340
I just made it with what you had. Enjoy.

23
00:02:32,340 --> 00:02:34,360
Thank you for the food.

24
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,720
Who is it at this hour?

25
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:39,780
Who is it?

26
00:02:39,780 --> 00:02:42,400
Did you order something?

27
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:47,230
They wouldn't come up here to deliver it. They would leave it downstairs.

28
00:02:47,230 --> 00:02:50,520
Didn't you lock the door?

29
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:54,050
I forgot. I wasn't in my right mind.

30
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:56,900
Who is it?

31
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:05,000
My son is here, isn't he?

32
00:03:05,770 --> 00:03:07,310
What?

33
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:11,160
Mom!

34
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:25,380
Mom, why are you here so suddenly?

35
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:28,040
Be quiet. I don't want to hear your voice.

36
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:31,010
Mom, you know I was going to try and call, but

37
00:03:31,010 --> 00:03:33,260
the restaurant somehow...

38
00:04:11,550 --> 00:04:13,220
Mom.

39
00:04:25,740 --> 00:04:27,140
 ?

40
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:32,570
 The spy who fell in love with me

41
00:04:32,570 --> 00:04:35,370
Gosh, you can skip over the cannons and get the general.

42
00:04:35,370 --> 00:04:37,660
- What are you doing?
 - Yes! Right. Right.

43
00:04:37,660 --> 00:04:39,780
That is not right!

44
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:41,590
Don't move.

45
00:04:41,590 --> 00:04:43,250
Will you be quiet?

46
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:45,510
Check!

47
00:04:45,510 --> 00:04:49,120
You, gramps, why butt into other's chess moves?

48
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,350
Is Myeong Dong here?

49
00:04:50,350 --> 00:04:54,120
Aigoo, what's wrong with me? My old lady told me to buy some spring onions, but I forgot.

50
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,800
Let's go.

51
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:59,270
Check mate. It's your turn.

52
00:04:59,270 --> 00:05:03,460
What are you doing? You have to take the chariot.

53
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:05,920
You have to get rid of it.

54
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:11,040
Aigoo, I guess there was that brilliant move left!

55
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:15,260
Good Idea. Good! Good! Good!

56
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:16,830
Check!

57
00:05:16,830 --> 00:05:21,350
You always complain when others butt in. Why do you...

58
00:05:23,850 --> 00:05:26,900
Fine. You're giving me great tips.

59
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,770
Here. It's my move.

60
00:05:29,770 --> 00:05:32,130
Are you going to keep playing?

61
00:05:42,670 --> 00:05:45,690
How is the chicken joint doing?

62
00:05:45,690 --> 00:05:48,260
Oh, good!

63
00:05:48,260 --> 00:05:52,720
They got suspended for two months.

64
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:57,710
Will they go out of business?

65
00:05:57,710 --> 00:06:00,260
Why? So you can butt in?

66
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:02,700
Nonsense.

67
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:09,880
Thinking about getting new tenants gives me a headache.

68
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:14,410
My kid seems to really like that place as well.

69
00:06:14,410 --> 00:06:18,580
Well, well. I think you want to butt in.

70
00:06:18,580 --> 00:06:20,980
I said thats not it!

71
00:06:22,420 --> 00:06:27,810
If I butt into young people's matters, I'll be an old fool.

72
00:06:28,590 --> 00:06:34,220
So you're saying you don't want to be an old fool?

73
00:06:38,410 --> 00:06:39,590
Check!

74
00:06:39,590 --> 00:06:42,710
What, what is this?

75
00:06:42,710 --> 00:06:47,730
Aigoo, aigoo, geez. Aigoo, my goodness, goodness.

76
00:06:48,410 --> 00:06:51,580
Will they really go out of business?

77
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:05,950
What are you doing here?

78
00:07:05,950 --> 00:07:08,680
Well, the thing is...

79
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:14,540
What is it?

80
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:18,500
Hold on, the mood right now is a bit...

81
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:19,850
What are you saying?

82
00:07:19,850 --> 00:07:22,110
Wait here for now.

83
00:07:31,030 --> 00:07:35,100
I gave him a check-up the other day. He is fine, Mom.

84
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:37,370
Right, I'm fine.

85
00:07:37,370 --> 00:07:41,230
A lot of office workers come to our hospital. Office workers are having a hard time these days.

86
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:43,090
They're overworked and tired.

87
00:07:43,090 --> 00:07:44,810
Yes. When I was working at a company—

88
00:07:44,810 --> 00:07:46,290
I told you to be quiet.

89
00:07:46,290 --> 00:07:48,890
I'm sorry, Mom.

90
00:07:49,530 --> 00:07:52,260
Buy some medicine and take it to your sibling.

91
00:07:52,260 --> 00:07:53,990
I will pay for it.

92
00:07:53,990 --> 00:07:57,830
You don't have to pay. I'll cover it.

93
00:07:59,990 --> 00:08:05,190
How much time do you need? When do you plan to close this place?

94
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:08,710
It might look like this now, but

95
00:08:08,710 --> 00:08:14,030
our shop was doing so well, we were about to become stable.

96
00:08:18,170 --> 00:08:22,930
I was wrong for not telling you, but

97
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:30,510
I'm not closing the shop. I'm not just trying this out.

98
00:08:33,020 --> 00:08:38,330
While looking for you, I searched every single store in this town.

99
00:08:38,330 --> 00:08:43,630
Every time I opened a store door, how do you think I felt?

100
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:47,750
I tried to understand you.

101
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:51,060
I thought, can this be a café,

102
00:08:51,060 --> 00:08:54,540
or this wine bar, this restaurant?

103
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:59,370
Why would you leave your company and go through this hardship?

104
00:08:59,370 --> 00:09:03,760
Each time I opened a door, I thought it over, worried, and made an effort.

105
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:08,050
This isn't it.

106
00:09:08,050 --> 00:09:10,250
What exactly do I have to understand?

107
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:13,230
Why this is not it, and why it won't work?

108
00:09:14,310 --> 00:09:16,190
A chicken shop?

109
00:09:17,340 --> 00:09:19,450
Oh, my goodness.

110
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:22,070
My head.

111
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:31,830
Don't see me out. I can't even look at you two.

112
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:44,680
Are you leaving?

113
00:09:47,460 --> 00:09:49,820
- Let me see your phone 
 - What?

114
00:09:49,820 --> 00:09:52,320
Don't you think you have something to tell me?

115
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:55,850
Right now isn't good, I'll get in touch with you.

116
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,690
Sure.

117
00:10:01,780 --> 00:10:03,590
That's my number.

118
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:16,120
Is it okay to let Mom leave by herself?

119
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,830
She told us not to follow her.

120
00:10:17,830 --> 00:10:23,090
For now, it is best to keep our distance. Nothing we say will work.

121
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:25,460
Right.

122
00:10:34,380 --> 00:10:36,140
Who was that just now?

123
00:10:36,140 --> 00:10:37,990
My mom.

124
00:10:37,990 --> 00:10:40,650
Your mother is quite something.

125
00:10:40,650 --> 00:10:43,580
Are you okay?

126
00:10:43,580 --> 00:10:47,190
I'm okay, but I'm worried about my mom.

127
00:10:47,190 --> 00:10:51,510
But now she went to my house, right?

128
00:10:51,510 --> 00:10:53,620
Where do I go after work?

129
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:55,730
Do you want to stay here too?

130
00:10:55,730 --> 00:10:57,970
Are you kidding?

131
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:06,420
Well, then you can leave. We are quite busy.

132
00:11:06,420 --> 00:11:10,390
Are we busy? Why?

133
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:17,250
What is all this?

134
00:11:17,250 --> 00:11:20,400
We are closed. Why did you order so much oil?

135
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:23,270
First, let's move it inside.

136
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:30,420
He told you to move it inside.

137
00:11:30,420 --> 00:11:33,060
I really should have come ten minutes later.

138
00:11:36,850 --> 00:11:39,360
Let go. It's heavy.

139
00:11:49,470 --> 00:11:51,310
What is this?

140
00:11:51,310 --> 00:11:55,320
It's not like you have money to waste. Why did you order so much oil?

141
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:59,880
Anyway, I don't think the sauce was the problem.

142
00:12:06,140 --> 00:12:07,160
 There are some of you who don't know about this place yet!

143
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:09,200
 If you like fried chicken, then this place is a must. Great store name too, Refreshing Bath Chicken.

144
00:12:10,780 --> 00:12:12,370
 The fried chicken is super crispy. Daebak!

145
00:12:12,370 --> 00:12:14,820
 When I first tried this place, it was great. But yesterday, it was so-so. I'm disappointed.

146
00:12:14,820 --> 00:12:19,850
When I checked SNS, there were some people saying that the taste was just so-so,

147
00:12:19,850 --> 00:12:23,720
even after we changed the menu to only offer fried chicken.

148
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:26,760
But on the same day,

149
00:12:26,760 --> 00:12:31,530
a lot of people were saying that it's super tasty and awesome.

150
00:12:31,530 --> 00:12:36,160
We're back to square one then. Even our fried chicken doesn't have consistency.

151
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:37,220
Yes.

152
00:12:37,220 --> 00:12:40,520
So I was thinking it over. After we reduced the menu,

153
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:46,150
we checked the seasoning carefully and the batter mix shouldn't cause any inconsistencies.

154
00:12:46,150 --> 00:12:50,910
I think the oil was the problem.

155
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:54,180
Why would the oil affect the taste?

156
00:12:54,180 --> 00:12:55,380
People don't taste the oil.

157
00:12:55,380 --> 00:12:57,470
Oil is important too.

158
00:12:57,470 --> 00:12:59,980
You first taste the seasoning after biting into the chicken,

159
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:06,330
then you taste the powder. But the final aftertaste in your mouth is the oil.

160
00:13:06,330 --> 00:13:07,060
Right.

161
00:13:07,060 --> 00:13:10,980
What I am saying is that I paid attention even to the oil.

162
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:15,590
I used brown rice oil for more crispiness and mixed in canola oil for a clean flavor.

163
00:13:15,590 --> 00:13:16,760
You know too

164
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:22,220
how hard I tried to get the best ratio for the brown rice oil and canola oil mix.

165
00:13:22,220 --> 00:13:23,790
Of course, I know.

166
00:13:23,790 --> 00:13:28,760
But do you know how much chicken we fry in the oil?

167
00:13:30,970 --> 00:13:31,560
That...

168
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:35,000
we change the oil once every two days.

169
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:38,230
We switch out one of the fryers every day.

170
00:13:38,230 --> 00:13:40,820
Isn't that pretty often?

171
00:13:42,350 --> 00:13:44,330
That was the problem.

172
00:13:44,330 --> 00:13:48,730
We counted the days to change the oil, not how many chickens we fried.

173
00:13:48,730 --> 00:13:51,680
I think that, too.

174
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:57,050
When we got a lot customers unexpectedly, the oil went bad faster.

175
00:13:57,860 --> 00:13:59,000
Let's try frying it.

176
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:03,150
To see how many chickens we can fry and maintain the same taste.

177
00:14:11,490 --> 00:14:12,770
Producer Beom.

178
00:14:12,770 --> 00:14:14,900
Senior.

179
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:15,830
Thank you.

180
00:14:15,830 --> 00:14:17,720
How is it?

181
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:20,320
I looked into it.

182
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:23,120
They don't have any records. They don't seem bad.

183
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:25,600
They? Which of the three?

184
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:29,820
Why ask? All three were in on it.

185
00:14:29,820 --> 00:14:33,880
You found something, right. What is it?

186
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:40,790
I shouldn't be telling you this.

187
00:14:40,790 --> 00:14:44,520
Why, what is it?

188
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:50,230
Have you read..."The Melodrama King on Campus"?

189
00:14:50,230 --> 00:14:51,660
What?

190
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:54,880
You know, that webtoon.

191
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:58,340
It's really popular.

192
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:09,560
What should I do? You came all the way here.

193
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:12,020
My job is not TV broadcasting, I'm a webtoon artist.

194
00:15:12,020 --> 00:15:15,900
- As an artist, I communicate through my work 
 - Ah.

195
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:17,650
I asked to see you because—

196
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:22,220
Since you came all the way here, I have a new idea I was thinking of.

197
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:26,140
I only work on my series, so I am always here.

198
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:28,950
I don't know what's going on in the world.

199
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:33,320
If you take a look at my business card, you'll realise that I'm not in variety, but—

200
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:35,780
Exactly, I didn't know that.

201
00:15:35,780 --> 00:15:40,350
I don't know even after seeing your business card. I make cute mistakes.

202
00:15:44,860 --> 00:15:48,340
If it's not a variety show, what do you do?

203
00:15:48,340 --> 00:15:50,610
Ah!
  Culture and Current Events

204
00:15:50,610 --> 00:15:54,220
Culture and current events, like real life documentaries?

205
00:15:54,220 --> 00:15:59,050
No, I'm doing a best restaurants show.

206
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:04,200
So the reason I came here is—

207
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,710
Are you telling me to cook?

208
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:09,240
That doesn't sound too bad.

209
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:12,760
When I cook, I don't know if it's salt or sugar.

210
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:14,880
I just sprinkle some and it tastes good.

211
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:17,300
Excuse me, Writer.

212
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:20,060
Can you let me speak?

213
00:16:20,990 --> 00:16:22,990
Okay, okay.

214
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:28,390
Do you know this person?

215
00:16:28,390 --> 00:16:32,160
How would I know just from a photo...?

216
00:16:33,050 --> 00:16:34,350
I know.

217
00:16:34,350 --> 00:16:36,420
Do you remember?

218
00:16:37,660 --> 00:16:39,870
What about these jerks?

219
00:16:40,590 --> 00:16:45,330
I'm personally investigating something related to these three.

220
00:16:45,330 --> 00:16:49,780
I heard they had done something awful to you.

221
00:16:49,780 --> 00:16:53,600
They did, because of these guys I couldn't eat

222
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:56,030
or sleep properly.

223
00:16:56,030 --> 00:16:57,950
That time I was hurt too deeply.

224
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:01,890
Can you explain in detail what they did to you?

225
00:17:01,890 --> 00:17:05,880
They wrote negative comments on my work.

226
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:06,530
What?

227
00:17:06,530 --> 00:17:08,960
So I reported them to the cyber investigation department.

228
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:12,820
I wanted to see who the heck they were.

229
00:17:12,820 --> 00:17:16,620
But they are Seo Bo Ah's friends after all.

230
00:17:16,620 --> 00:17:17,660
Seo Bo Ah?

231
00:17:17,660 --> 00:17:22,020
She said her friends made a mistake and begged.

232
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:24,570
So I settled with them and ended it.

233
00:17:24,570 --> 00:17:28,630
Why? Did they cause another incident?

234
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:30,750
Seo Bo Ah?

235
00:17:35,460 --> 00:17:38,100
Now it's a little crooked.

236
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:40,230
How about now?

237
00:17:40,990 --> 00:17:42,890
Okay, it's good.

238
00:17:42,890 --> 00:17:43,890
Is it alright?

239
00:17:43,890 --> 00:17:45,260
Yes.

240
00:17:45,260 --> 00:17:47,150
Okay.

241
00:17:54,180 --> 00:17:55,720
Turn it on.

242
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:57,580
Yes.

243
00:18:05,330 --> 00:18:07,770
 Refreshing Bath: Barun Chicken

244
00:18:07,770 --> 00:18:12,330
When our suspension is over, I'll make a flyer saying we fry only 58 chickens with one tub of oil.

245
00:18:12,330 --> 00:18:14,720
I'll draw it prettily.

246
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:17,370
Thank you, Bo Ah.

247
00:18:17,370 --> 00:18:19,490
You can turn it off again.

248
00:18:22,680 --> 00:18:28,330
Now the issue with the recipe is resolved and we could do really well if we can start again,

249
00:18:28,330 --> 00:18:31,100
but we can't open the store.

250
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:33,490
Just a month and a half.

251
00:18:33,490 --> 00:18:39,060
But what should we do with the fried chicken we made?

252
00:18:39,060 --> 00:18:40,770
We can't sell them.

253
00:18:40,770 --> 00:18:42,010
Right.

254
00:18:42,010 --> 00:18:45,890
Then can I take a few that we just fried?

255
00:18:45,890 --> 00:18:49,260
Me too. I just need one.

256
00:18:50,980 --> 00:18:52,550
Fine.

257
00:19:42,150 --> 00:19:44,860
Chicken's here!

258
00:19:58,810 --> 00:20:02,000
How is it, grandfather?

259
00:20:03,210 --> 00:20:04,750
What is it?

260
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:08,560
Do you think I only visit you to ask favors?

261
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:12,530
- Grandfather? 
 - What?

262
00:20:12,530 --> 00:20:17,650
What would you do if I wanted to open a chicken restaurant?

263
00:20:17,650 --> 00:20:20,080
What do you think?

264
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:23,520
If you would live a normal life,

265
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:25,630
I would welcome anything.

266
00:20:25,630 --> 00:20:28,200
No, think about it seriously.

